stimulus:
The following text is from the 1923 poem “Black
Finger” by Angelina Weld
Grimké, a Black American
writer. A cypress is a type of evergreen tree.

I have just seen a most beautiful thing,
Slim and still,
Against a gold, gold sky,
A straight black cypress,
Sensitive,
Exquisite,
A black finger
Pointing upwards.
Why, beautiful still finger, are you black?
And why are you pointing upwards?

Which choice best describes the overall structure of
the text?

choices.A:
The speaker assesses a natural phenomenon,
then questions the accuracy of her assessment.
choices.B:
The speaker describes a distinctive sight in
nature, then ponders what meaning to attribute
to that sight.
choices.C:
The speaker presents an outdoor scene, then
considers a human behavior occurring within
that scene.
choices.D:
The speaker examines her surroundings, then
speculates about their influence on her
emotional state.
